    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Alchemilla truncata are skin irritations such as eczema, which are often caused by allergies or irritants and can be relieved by its anti-inflammatory properties. It has also been used to treat wounds, including cuts and abrasions, by promoting healing and reducing the risk of infection. Alchemilla truncata's anti-inflammatory properties also make it effective in soothing joint pain and inflammation associated with conditions like arthritis. Furthermore, its astringent properties make it useful in treating mouth sores and gum inflammation. Additionally, its antiseptic properties have been used to treat minor burns, promoting healing and reducing the risk of infection.",
