    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Alchemilla truncata are its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids, saponins, and volatile oils. The plant's anti-inflammatory properties help to reduce the risk of infection and promote wound healing, making it useful in the treatment of skin conditions and injuries. Alchemilla truncata also exhibits antioxidant properties, which protect cells from oxidative damage and may contribute to its ability to reduce the risk of certain diseases. Its antimicrobial properties, particularly against bacterial and fungal pathogens, make it a valuable component in traditional medicine for treating infections and promoting a healthy immune system. The plant's antiseptic properties, resulting from the action of its bioactive compounds, help to prevent the spread of infection and promote a speedy recovery in cases of wound infection or injury.",
