    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Alchemilla truncata are flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol, tannins like epicatechin, and phenolic acids like gallic acid, along with its high content of ascorbic acid. These constituents are responsible for its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties, which contribute to its wound-healing effects. Studies have shown that flavonoids in Alchemilla truncata can inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, reducing inflammation and tissue damage. The tannins and phenolic acids have been found to exhibit antimicrobial activity, helping to prevent infection and promote wound healing. The high ascorbic acid content contributes to its antioxidant properties, which protect the wound from oxidative stress and promote tissue repair.",
