    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Alchemilla truncata are derived from its leaves, which are rich in tannins, flavonoids, and other bioactive compounds. Infusion of the leaves is used topically to treat skin irritations, wounds, and minor burns, due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. Tincture of Alchemilla truncata is used internally to treat gastrointestinal issues, such as diarrhea and dyspepsia, due to its astringent and anti-inflammatory effects. Salve and ointment preparations are used topically to treat skin conditions, including eczema and dermatitis, due to their soothing and protective properties. Tea prepared from the leaves is used internally to treat fever, rheumatism, and other inflammatory conditions, due to its anti-inflammatory and analgesic effects.",
